Frustrated commuters are alleged to be behind the incident, in which three carriages were set alight on Monday. CAPE TOWN - Frustrated commuters are alleged to be behind an incident in which three train carriages were set alight on Monday.Metrorail's Riana Scott says the service had infrastructural problems on Monday evening. This forced trains to terminate at Nyanga while technicians were solving the problem. It seems commuter frustration boiled over and the train was torched. Last week, eight coaches were gutted in an arson attack at Cape Town Station and some shops were damaged.WATCH: 8 train carriages destroyed in chaos at Cape Town Train StationThey became angry over lengthy delays in train schedules.One person was arrested.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)